All of the &quot;posts&quot;, in this site, have included the language<br>
that was USED, back then, during &quot;the war&quot;. This language<br>
reflected the frustration of the times, whether you considered yourself pro-war or anti-war. Anyone using this<br>
site for the purpose of being some kind of moderator/censor/diplomat, I feel, misunderstands the purpose of this site. History is REAL. History is NOT a study in acceptable language/etiquette. I believe the purpose of this site, is to inform those that didn't really<br>
LIVE (or AVOIDED living) the Viet Nam &quot;years&quot;, exactly what<br>
that period of time MEANT to those that DID participate in<br>
REAL life, back then.  
